      "role": "user",
      "content": "The \"ledger\" idea makes sense. I can probably implement a lightweight wrapper. \n\nOne thing that's worrying me though is that even with better tracking, I'm worried about things getting \"lost\" or corrupted in ways that don't show up as a simple leak, but rather as weird, unpredictable state changes. How do I keep an eye out for those more subtle, \"hidden\" errors that don't just eat RAM but actually mess with the data integrity?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
